1 S.P. 10
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 VETERANS AND LEGAL AFFAIRS
4 Reproduced and distributed under the direction of the Secretary of the Senate.
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 10, “JOINT RESOLUTION MAKING
10 SEPARATE APPLICATIONS TO THE CONGRESS OF THE UNITED STATES
11 CALLING ARTICLE V CONVENTIONS TO PROPOSE AMENDMENTS
12 ESTABLISHING TERM LIMITS FOR MEMBERS OF CONGRESS AND TERM
13 LIMITS FOR JUSTICES OF THE UNITED STATES SUPREME COURT”
14 Amend the resolution by striking out the title and substituting the following:
15 'JOINT RESOLUTION MAKING APPLICATION TO THE CONGRESS OF THE
16 UNITED STATES CALLING AN ARTICLE V CONVENTION TO PROPOSE AN
17 AMENDMENT ESTABLISHING TERM LIMITS FOR MEMBERS OF
18 CONGRESS'
19 Amend the resolution by inserting after the first resolved paragraph the following:
20 'RESOLVED: That the Legislature of Maine directs any delegates to a convention
21 called for as a result of this application to be limited to considering and proposing
22 amendments within the scope of this application; and be it further'
23 Amend the resolution by striking out all of the 3rd and 4th resolved paragraphs.
24 Amend the resolution in the 5th resolved paragraph in the first line by striking out the
25 following: "these applications constitute continuing applications" and inserting the
26 following: 'this application constitutes a continuing application'
27 Amend the resolution in the 5th resolved paragraph in the last line by striking out the
28 following: "subjects" and inserting the following: 'subject'
29 Amend the resolution by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
30 section number to read consecutively.
31 SUMMARY
3322 This amendment removes the provisions within the joint resolution making a separate
3333 application to the Congress of the United States calling an Article V convention to propose
3344 an amendment establishing term limits for justices of the United States Supreme Court.
